\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 109. D. strictus }Banks & Solander in A. Russell, {\i Nat. Hist. Aleppo} ed. 2, {\b 2}: 252 (1794) ({\i D. multipunctatus }Ser.). Glabrous perennial 30-50 cm, with woody stock and simple or branched stems. Basal leaves withered at anthesis; cauline 1-3 mm wide, acuminate, 6-12 pairs, about as long as internodes. Epicalyx-scales 1/3 as long as calyx, ovate, cuspidate, broadly scarious. Calyx 15-18 mm, conical, verruculose, unribbed but with purple lines on the teeth continued downwards from sinuses. Petal-limb c. 10 mm, dentate, bearded. 2n = 30.{\i  W. Kriti.} Cr. ({\i S.W. Asia}.)
