\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 110. D. tripunctatus }Sm. in Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr. }{\b 1}: 286 (1809). Divaricately-branched, glabrous annual 15-40 cm. Basal leaves usually withered at anthesis, 3-8 mm wide, oblong-spathulate, obtuse; cauline leaves linear, acuminate. Epicalyx-scales c. ¾ as long as calyx, ovate with a long, usually green, subulate apex. Calyx c. 15 mm, conical, broadly ribbed and verruculose on sides of ribs, glabrous. Petal-limb c. 10 mm, dentate, bearded, with 3 red spots at base.{\i  S. Greece and Aegean region; Italy} ({\i Calabria, Elba}). Cr Gr It [Lu].
